How Not to Lose Clients to iBuyers

 Jun 24, 2019

Jun 24, 2019

Telling the right stories can help you secure more clients, and today I’ll explain how.

I recently read an article that explained how sellers lost $14 billion in equity last year because of the increasing number of iBuyers entering our market. Selling to these companies is usually advertised as a convenient deal, but is actually a very ineffective move for today’s sellers. 

So, what can you do to dissuade sellers from going that route? One of the simplest ways is by doing what you do best: offering expert real estate advice.

“You can use personal success stories of the clients you’ve helped to secure future clients.”

Given that 71% of buyers are afraid to buy a home that needs work, some of the best advice you can offer sellers is to make strategic repairs. The right repairs and upgrades will not only bring a high return, but they’ll also help sellers to close quickly and for top dollar. 

Once you’ve guided a seller to closing using this (or any other tips), you can use the success stories that come out of these experiences to help you secure future clients who might have otherwise considered selling to an iBuyer.

If you have any other questions or would like more information, feel free to give me a call or send me an email. I look forward to hearing from you soon.

    • About Nate Martinez


    Nate Martinez, REALTOR®, Owner, Team Leader, Master Coach, International Bestselling Author, Coach, ABR, CRS, GRI, e-PRO, CDPE, CIAS, CLHMS, CRP, and SFR

    Nate Martinez is the owner of RE/MAX Professionals, a multi-office franchise located in the greater Phoenix area and the owner of a Motto Mortgage franchise. The highlight of running his business and team is getting to work in the trenches every day with the love of his life and his adult children. In 2021, he co-authored an international bestselling book, 8 Ways to Dominate Any Real Estate Market with long-time business partner, team member and friend, Sarah Michelle Bliss.

    Nate passionately believes in the value of education, having trained hundreds of real estate professionals across the globe as a speaker and a coach. With more than thirty-five years in the real estate industry, he has been recognized with the Lifetime Achievement, Titan Team, Circle of Legends, and the Luminary of Distinction from RE/MAX. But with all these achievements, Nate’s focus has always been giving back to this industry and now focuses much of his time on helping agents discover their potential and ultimately live their best life.

    He is most proud of the charitable contributions of his agents to the Children’s Miracle Network and the support of their local Phoenix Children’s Hospital. In addition, he is proud to be ranked the number one brokerage in Arizona when it comes to production per agent.

    Outside of work, Nate enjoys golfing and spending quality time around the pool with his adult children and their spouses, his confidant Tonya, their daughter, Mila, and three grandchildren.
